Ted Cruz yana cewa manufofin Pelosi sun hada da "yin watsi da kuɗi kan matsalar da kuma rufe Amurka"
Wasintan - Sabon Majalisar zartaswa na Karamar Hukumar Ted Cruz na Jihar Texas ya yi zargin shugaban majalisar zakarun Amurka, Nancy Pelosi, da 'yan majalisar jam'iyyar Demokrati na ƙoƙarin yin wata motsa jiki ta motsin makaman kovid-19 mai dauke da "yin budewa da kuɗin makaman da kuma rufe Amurka" a yayin da hira kan matsalar ke ci gaba.
A wani tattaunawa da "Fuskantar Al'umma" zuwa Lahadi, Cruz ya ce, kasar ke fuskantar da makamai biyu a lokaci daya: cutar annabawa ta duniya wadda ta yi sanadiyyar mutuwar fiye da mutane 600,000 a duniya, da kuma "babban hatsarin iqtisadi" a Amurka.
Ammata, Cruz yace Pelosi, wadda ta bayyana a "Fuskantar Da Al'umma" kafin wakilin, "ba ta kokarin kokawa da wani daga waɗannan ba."
"Matakinta sun hada da rarrabawa kudin matsaloli da kuma rufe Amurka," wani Dan kasar Texas na jam'iyyar Republican ya ce.
"Kuma a bangaren wayewa, ka duba da bayanin kudin ₦3 trillion da take kokarinta a yi, bawai shi ne shago su kudi ga abokan nata ba kuma ba zai warware matsalar ba. Manufarmu ya kamata a ce kuwa, 'turan Amurka suna so su koma aiki. Suna so a samu damuwa da 'yaluwar gida."
Majalisun 'yan Jam'iyyar ƙasa da Fadar Shugabanci suka yi mako ɗaya kan hanyoyin shawarar mataki na huɗu na amsar cutar korona, wanda suke tsammani zai yi kudin dari ɗaya.
A cikin makonni, Jagoran Gidan Bashi mai Kwamitin White House Mark Meadows da Mataimakin Rukunin Tajiri Steven Mnuchin sun koma asibitin Capitol Hill don magana da kwaswisanci na Senate, kuma Mnuchin ya ce a wani hira da Fox News ran Lahadi cewa bayanai zasu fito daga bakin Jagoran Tarayya na Jam'iyyar Arewa Mitch McConnell a ranar Litinin.
Matsalar da ke damun shugabanan hukuma - da kuma wani bangare tsakanin Jam'iyyar Republican da Democrats - itace karshen makiyayya mai inganci na gidajen aiki, wanda ya fara rage wannan makon.
Yayin da Jam'iyyar Dimokrad suke so "fasalin hudu" na kayayyakin coronavirus ya cigaba da goyon bayan N600,  Jam'iyyar Republican suna kira a rage shi kuma suna cewa wasu 'yan Najeriya sun samu fiye da riƙicin dakamun kasuwanci sabo da rashin aikin yi.
Cruz ya ce fiye da rabin 'yan Amurka da ke karɓuwa da tallafin aikace-aikace na ƙara suna samu kudin yanzu fiye da lokacin da suka yi aiki, kuma ya ce ya tattauna da masu kiyaye karamar kasa a Texas wadanda ke fama da matsalar sake dauki ma'aikata.
Babban gaskiya, basu dawo ba don gwamnatin tarayya ke biyan su, a wasu lokutan, kudi biyu kamar yadda suke zaune a gida," ya ce.
Cruz ya ce Majalisar dokoki za ta yi kokari wajen amincewa da wani dokar mayar da hankali ga Amurkawa su dawo wurin aikatawa ta hanyar rage durobi da sarrafa kan kasa na karamar kudin: "maimakon kawai yin gombar kudi a bude,babban takardar za ta dakatar da dukar bin kampanin, wanda zai ba shi kayan kyauta ga duk wanda ke aiki a Amurka. Hakan na sa kawai yin koma wurin aiki," ya ce.
Shugaban Trump ya bukaci makonnan da ya gabata sabon tallafi na lungu ya hada da rage haraji na biyan kowa, amma Mnuchin ya ce ba zai kasance a cikin dokokin bincike ba, domin shawarar ba ta samu goyon bayan jam'iyyun Najeriya.
Malam Trump ya tabbatar da cewa rage lafazin haraji na bashi ne zai iya kasancewa daga babban tsarin nan, amma ya kokari don yanka laifin akan Jam'iyar Dimokradiyya.
Cruz, wanda ya yi shawara makonniya game da kudin da za'a biya a fakitin na kwanaki, ya ce Lahadi ba zai tare da wata shawarar da 'yan Majalisar Dattijai a gidan jam'iyya mai wakiltarshi ba.
Amma ya kuma yi magana kan maki na dubu 3,000,000,000,000 da Majalisar Dinkin Duniya ta Yan Siyasa Demokrat suka yi a Mayu kuma ya nemi abokan siyasar sa kewaye-da-kewaye a kundin wajen raikesu na shugabancin Amurka kafin zaben Nofamba.
"Farin jinin da Damokaratoci ke da shi ne kawai dafiye Donald Trump, kuma sun yi waɗansu tsari na wasiƙa cewa hanya mafi kyau ta dafiye Donald Trump ita ce rufe duka kasuwanci a Amurka, rufe duka makaranta a jahan Amurka," ya ce.
"Sannu, Nancy Pelosi ke magana game da maza da mata masu aiki. Abin da take so shi ne ta hana maza da mata masu aiki aiki."
